    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Jackson Merrill** (75.10) and **Kyle Tucker** (70.51), who both benefit from a prime matchup against Michael McGreevy. **Jackson Merrill** is our strongest play; his leadoff role combined with a plus-matchup against a 4.35 xERA pitcher and a significant boost from his stolen base potential against a slow-delivery pitcher makes him a set-and-forget anchor. Similarly, **Jacob Wilson** (68.37) earns a top-tier slot today, largely due to a favorable leadoff assignment and a solid +8% boost from the SP skill profile of Slade Cecconi. **Drake Baldwin** (66.86) rounds out our elite grouping, with his projected #2 spot in the order offering an excellent multiplier on a high-base projection, effectively leveraging his recent offensive momentum.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench centered on **Coby Mayo** (49.90), who narrowly missed the cut behind **Nasim Nunez** (50.97). While **Coby Mayo** benefits from the stolen base opportunities presented by Weathers' slow delivery, his projected #8 spot created a drag on his efficiency score that kept him pinned to the bench. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Gunnar Henderson** (57.16); despite the base power, he faces a negative platoon split against Weathers, which tempers his overall outlook today. We remain cautious regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for nearly the entire roster, as sudden shifts in batting orders\u2014specifically for players like **Liam Hicks** or **Dominic Smith**\u2014could force real-time adjustments to preserve our games-played cap. Ensure that all starters are confirmed before first pitch, as the high-volatility nature of these marginal scoring plays means any downgrade in lineup position will necessitate a shift toward our bench depth.",
